3. Of old was the age &caesura; when Ymir lived;

Sea nor cool waves &caesura; nor sand there were;

Earth had not been, &caesura; nor heaven above,

But a yawning gap, &caesura; and grass nowhere.

45. Brothers shall fight &caesura; and fell each other,

And sisters' sons &caesura; shall kinship stain;


Hard is it on earth, &caesura; with mighty whoredom;

Axe-time, sword-time, &caesura; shields are sundered,

Wind-time, wolf-time, &caesura; ere the world falls;

Nor ever shall men &caesura; each other spare.

50. From the east comes Hrym &caesura; with shield held high;

In giant-wrath &caesura; does the serpent writhe;

O'er the waves he twists, &caesura; and the tawny eagle

Gnaws corpses screaming; &caesura; Naglfar is loose.
